messages.content: What is the purpose of the graphNavigator extension in ComfyUI?
graphNavigator is a ComfyUI Web Extension created to help navigate large ComfyUI graph workflows.
How can I save the current view in graphNavigator?
To save the current view in graphNavigator, click the disk icon.
How can I rename a view in graphNavigator?
To rename a view in graphNavigator, double-click the view name or right-click and select 'Rename' from the context menu.
How can I delete a view in graphNavigator?
To delete a view in graphNavigator, right-click on the view and select 'Delete' from the context menu.
How can I rearrange views in graphNavigator?
To rearrange views in graphNavigator, drag and drop the views to change their order.
How can I switch between the first 12 views using keyboard shortcuts in graphNavigator?
To switch between the first 12 views in graphNavigator, use the keyboard shortcut (ctrl-shift-Fn), where Fn is the corresponding view number.
How do I install the graphNavigator extension?
To install graphNavigator, place the graphNavigator folder in your ComfyUI\web\extensions directory and restart ComfyUI.
What is a planned feature for graphNavigator?
A planned feature for graphNavigator is to save views with the png data, allowing custom views for each image/workflow.
